\int_0^\infty \frac{1}{x^2+1} \, dx=\dfrac{\pi}{2}
f(x)=\dfrac{1}{x^2+1}
\int_{x_{1}}^{x_{2}} f(x)\,dx+\int_{x_3}^{x_4} f(x)\,dx+\cdots +\int_{x_{2k+1}}^{x_{2k+2}} f(x)\,dx+\cdots
\int_{\Bbb{R}} g_{n} 
n \to \infty
 g_{n}(x) = f(x) \sum_{k=1}^{n} \mathbf{1}_{[x_{2k-1}, x_{2k}]}(x). 
0 \leq g_n \leq f
